  "text": "The LLVM optimization pass pipeline is structured as follows:\n\n1. **PassBuilder Class Definition** (llvm/include/llvm/Passes/PassBuilder.h, line 114): The PassBuilder class provides the interface for constructing optimization pipelines. It includes methods for registering analyses and building pass pipelines for different optimization levels.\n\n2. **Pass Manager Infrastructure** (llvm/include/llvm/IR/PassManager.h, line 162): The PassManager template class is the core execution engine. It implements PassManager<Module> and PassManager<Function> which manage execution of passes over IR units. The header defines PassInfoMixin template which provides metadata for passes.\n\n3. **Pipeline Construction** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassBuilderPipelines.cpp): This file contains the implementation of PassBuilder methods that construct the default optimization pipelines:\n   - buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline (line 1716): Builds the complete default module pipeline for a given optimization level\n   - buildModuleSimplificationPipeline (line 1091): Builds the simplification phase of the pipeline\n   - buildModuleOptimizationPipeline: Builds the optimization phase\n   The buildPerModuleDefaultPipeline method chains these together to create the full O0/O1/O2/O3 pipelines.\n\n4. **Pass Registry** (llvm/lib/Passes/PassRegistry.def): Central registry defining all standard passes using macro-based registration. Contains entries like \"FUNCTION_PASS(\\\"dse\\\", DSEPass())\" for registering individual passes with their names and instantiation code.\n\n5. **Concrete Example: DeadStoreElimination**:\n   - Header: llvm/include/llvm/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.h\n   - Implementation: llvm/lib/Transforms/Scalar/DeadStoreElimination.cpp\n   - Class: DSEPass (inherits from PassInfoMixin<DSEPass>)\n   - The pass is registered in PassRegistry.def as \"dse\" and included in PassBuilderPipelines.cpp (line 96) where it's instantiated and added to function pass managers (lines 789, 2222)\n\nThe pipeline lifecycle flow: PassBuilder methods iterate through optimization levels, instantiate passes from PassRegistry.def, add them to appropriate pass managers (Module/Function/Loop), and PassManager executes them in sequence. Each pass like DSEPass implements a run() method that takes the IR unit and analysis manager, performing the actual optimization."
}

